			  			Yeah...im bored so i thought what the hell.<br />
<br />
If someone HAS to send out ALL their fleets to destroy someone elses and get those great URs in plain sight you leave your planet vulnerable right? 2 cruisers and any planet fails.  Well, that could really suck if it was you so how about a nice Planetary Defense Grid (*imagines mindwarper wincing at the though off the TONS of new code required*)<br />
Planetary Defense Grid: a network of turrent defenses designed to stop light to moderate attacks.<br />
<br />
like a bunch of turrents you can place on each planet. such as:<br />
Level 1)Plasma Turrent<br />
Level 2)Fusion Turrent<br />
Level 3)Anti-Matter Turrent<br />
Level 4)Time-Wake Homing Missle Turrent<br />
Level 5)Doomsday Ray Cannon<br />
<br />
Each turrent would have a certain cost of something appropriate to its damage, then raise the cost say 5% per turrent. The number of military bases on the planet would determine how many turrents of each level the planet could support.<br />
<br />
(*now wonderes if mindwarper was correct how much code this was take...BUT WAIT! im not done adding more code and headaches!*)<br />
<br />
What the hell, why not? i like getting flamed :)<br />
<br />
PLANETARY EQUIPTMENT! (devices)<br />
_________ = increases turrent hitpoints by __%<br />
_________ = increases turrent reload speed by __%<br />
_________ = gives turrents a __%chance to do critical hits<br />
<br />
(hold your flaiming im not done thinking of more headaches)<br />
strike that...unfortunantly iv run out of headaches for code makers....<br />
<br />
<br />
ALRIGHT ALRIGHT, you can start flaming me about how STUPID and COMPLICATED and how WRONG for archspace this is now ;)						<P align=right> </P>
