			  	hmmm. i was thinking the same thing as the defence platforms/starbases = ships with out engins. but now that i think of it why not just use the current ships? i cant really think of the advantages for immoble defences. in order to keep the game balanced they could not be cheaper, and they would have to have equivalante power rateing for fire power. it seems a moot point at the moment, just use the current ships. the military bases do need to be upgraded consiterably thoe, i meen come on 2 crusers conquering hundreds of millions of pplz? not probable. a moble fort or 2 maybe, a doomstar sure but not a meesely pair of crusers. i dont know much/anything about code writeing but i would think that simply upping the military base defence effictiveness would be easyest and most effictive answer. <br />
<br />
example formula: <br />
0% bases = no defence<br />
10% = can fend off small cruser fleets 50/50<br />
20-40% = battleships probabaly nesasry to defeat,<br />
large numbers of crusers could defeat but with heavy loses.<br />
50-70% = dreadnaughts + moble forts needed, ect<br />
80-100% = doomstars ect<br />
<br />
this would ofcourse need balanceing for planet size and tech level, but adds the needed depth for defence to offence.<br />
<br />
also this is balanced for the purpuses value to usefullness. say you have that ultrarich world you want to keep. you can make it vary hard to take but in doing so you drastically reduse its usfullness.<br />
this also helps one of the other questians of player deaths. if one of your planets is a fortress world you will be much harder to kill. it becomes much less desireable to kill off some one with a fortress because of the cost. this makes a nice fall back point/saftey net for new to moderate class players.<br />
<br />
